TEXT(beginproblem());


BEGIN_TEXT

For the curve given by 
\[ 
r(t) = \langle  \sin(t) - t \cos(t), \cos(t) +t \sin(t), $a t^2 + $b \rangle \]



$PAR 
Find the unit tangent $BR
\( T(t) = \langle \) \{ans_rule(20)\}, \{ans_rule(20)\}, \{ans_rule(20)\} \( \rangle \)
$PAR
Find the unit normal $BR
\( N(t) = \langle \) \{ans_rule(20)\}, \{ans_rule(20)\}, \{ans_rule(20)\} \( \rangle \)
$PAR
Find the curvature $BR
 \( \kappa (t) = \)  \{ans_rule(30)\} 

END_TEXT

$kap = 4*$a*$a + 1;
$temp = sqrt( 4*$a*$a + 1 );          #just to improve legibility
$ans1 = "sin(t) / $temp";
$ans2 = "cos(t) / $temp";
$ans3 = "2*$a / $temp";
$ans4 = "cos(t)";
$ans5 = "(-1)*sin(t)";
$ans6 = "0";
$ans7 = "1/($kap * t)";

ANS( function_cmp( $ans1, "t" ) );
ANS( function_cmp( $ans2, "t" ) );
ANS( function_cmp( $ans3, "t") );
ANS( function_cmp( $ans4, "t" ) );
ANS( function_cmp( $ans5, "t" ) );
ANS( function_cmp( $ans6, "t") );
## ANS(num_cmp($ans7));
ANS( function_cmp( $ans7, "t") );



